white house urges nuclear inspectors to monitor north korea 's nuclear suspension
the white house on tuesday called for sending nuclear inspectors as soon as possible to monitor north korea 's closure of its nuclear reactor , after a telephone conversation between us president george w. bush and south korean president roh moo - hyun .
" today , the two leaders discussed the latest developments in cooperation between the united states and south korea on the north korean nuclear issue , and looked forward to the return of iaea inspectors to north korea soon in order to monitor the halt of operations and closure of north korea 's nuclear reactor , " said white house national security council spokesman gordon chiang .
charter pointed out that the two presidents also welcomed the us - south korea free trade agreement signed yesterday and would make every effort to ensure that the two countries ' congress approves this agreement .
experts believe that the plutonium that pyongyang has produced over the past 20 years is sufficient to produce 12 nuclear weapons .
after visiting pyongyang last week , us envoy to the six - party talks hill said he expected the yongbyon nuclear reactor to be closed in mid - july .
43 killed in west india torrential rain
strong winds and torrential rain hit western india during the weekend , seriously flooded some areas , and all domestic and overseas routes of bombay , the largest city in the west , were suspended .
a total of 43 people were killed , rescue officials said today .
from june to september each year , torrential rains brought about by monsoon rains often led to flooding in india , a country with 1.1 billion people , and even caused casualties .
in this torrential rain disaster , half of the victims were drowned and others died of power failure or power failure .
bombay , india 's financial center , has also been affected .
on the 29 th and 30 th alone , the rainfall in bombay reached 243 kilometers .
bombay 's chief executive bayan said that 13 people were killed in the city alone .
officials from the city government called on 15 million citizens not to go out of the city before the rainstorms in order to safeguard their own safety .
rain fell slightly yesterday , and flooded areas in bombay today .
nearly 500 dead in indian rainy season
according to officials and media reports , the death toll in india this year has risen to 474 due to rainstorms .
the press trust of india quoted minister for disaster relief and reconstruction kandan of the government as saying today that in the past week various indian provinces have entered the rainy season one after another . casualties and economic losses have been serious in various places . the death toll of mahathir , the province of bombay , the largest city of india , is now 358 .
the report pointed out that kardan made the above remarks to reporters during an inspection in bombay .
he said that as india 's biggest cotton producer , mahathir mohamad , the largest cotton producer in the country , was covered in a vast expanse of water . about two - thousand villages , including 27 towns and about two - thousand villages , suffered serious flooding and more than 10,000 disaster victims were moved to safe places of refuge .
the whole of india began to enter the rainy season one week ago . the people of all provinces welcomed the rain and rain with a feeling of being dry for a long time . however , it was unexpected that the rain was violent , the rain was disastrous , the highway became polluted , and the houses in low - lying areas were almost paralyzed . statistics show that nearly 500 people have died of floods .
