satellite image shows iran 's tunnel might be used to protect nuclear equipment
iran may have to protect its nuclear equipment in times of air raids , a commercial satellite image showed tuesday in a mountain tunnel near natanz uranium enrichment facility , the us think - tank science and international security institute said .
these images were taken by the us digital earth company ghazloe on june 11 and were posted on the website of the institute of science and international safety .
the research institute is based in washington , dc , and is a non - profit research organization .
the photos show that at only 2.4 kilometers south of natanz facility , road works are underway along the mountain , and the facility is a uranium enrichment plant .
analysts albright and bratislava pointed out in a report that the entrances and exits of the tunnel in the image are not clear , but " one of the roads seems to be connected to a tunnel facility , and another road may also be connected to the tunnel entrance and exit . "
they said : " this tunnel facility , which has been dug into the mountains , will play an excellent protection role during the air raid . "
iran remains tough in nuclear talks : un envoy
the united nations atomic energy agency ( iaea ) today held talks with iranian officials in tehran to try once again to break the deadlock over iran 's nuclear programme .
however , iranian president mahmoud ahmadinejad is still stubbornly clinging to the pressure of further un sanctions .
mahmoud ahmadinejad maintained that iran will not stop uranium enrichment but welcomed the latest talks .
he said , " the installation of centrifuges can slow down or accelerate . this is a question of implementation . however , no one should expect us to give up our rights . we will not stop this trend . "
he made the remarks after the arrival of tehran .
the purpose of hyoginin 's visit is to work out a set of plans to solve the " unsolved problems " over iran 's nuclear programme .
the united nations has imposed two sanctions on iran for tehran 's failure to freeze uranium enrichment work .
the iranian news agency reported that haiyongning held talks with officials led by the iranian national security supreme council assistant president vaidi .
iran 's talks group also includes the vice - president of the atomic energy agency , president of the atomic energy agency , and ambassador to the international atomic energy agency ( iaea ) soltaniyeh .
palestinian prime minister to form new government in emergency period
the palestinian authority was in a state of emergency for one month after hamas militants took over the gaza strip . prime minister farooq al - yaad temporarily resigned but was ordered to form a new government . "
minister of the agriculture and social affairs department habasit told afp : " prime minister jacques chirac submitted his resignation to president abbas . the president accepted the offer . meanwhile , he also asked him to form a new cabinet that is responsible for handling the routine administrative affairs . "
abbas ' trusted follower , mahmud , told afp that he had tendered his resignation while abbas ordered him to " perform his current duties until he was formed a new government . "
the respected economist faleer submitted his resignation , but the procedural resignation would not shake his position as the prime minister .
the palestinian emergency cabinet has been in charge of implementing the emergency orders announced by abbas after hamas committed violence against gaza since july 17 .
according to the basic law of the palestinian autonomous government , the state of emergency cannot exceed 30 days without the approval of the parliament , but the autonomous parliament is now paralyzed .
the authorization of the emergency government expired today .
wto representative moves to break deadlock in doha round of talks
major wto negotiating representatives today proposed that the united states significantly reduce its subsidies to agriculture and that developing countries significantly lower tariffs on industrial imports in order to break the deadlock of the doha round of trade talks .
officials said that the new " draft " model calls on the united states to lower its annual agricultural subsidies from the current $ 19 - billion to $ 16.2 - billion , and developing countries to lower the import tariffs on industrial products to less than 23 percent .
the proposals are aimed at breaking the deadlock of the doha round of talks over the past six years and bringing about compromise among 150 wto members .
wto secretary general pascal lamy said these proposals were " a fair and reasonable basis for reaching far - reaching goals , balancing relations , and taking development as the guide . "
" members are not completely satisfied with the contents of the proposal , but the current differences are less than the issues of consensus , " lamy said .
he called for intensive negotiations in the next few weeks .
japanese auto manufacturers cut production or production due to strong earthquake
automotive manufacturers such as toyota and nissan said tuesday they would cut production or even suspend production in japan because of a strong earthquake that has caused a shortage of parts for cars .
on sunday , an earthquake measuring 6.8 on the richter scale rocked japan , forcing a car parts manufacturer to suspend its operations at factories in northwestern tokyo and affecting its production .
toyota will suspend its production from tonight through the 21 st , a spokeswoman for the world 's best - selling toyota , said .
nissan will suspend partial production in three japanese factories from the day after tomorrow and will reassess the situation during the weekend , a company spokesman said .
he said that both factories had two production lines , one of which would be affected , but the company could increase its shift duties next month to make up for backward production progress .
suzuki said that japan 's fuji heavy industry corporation , which will suspend part of its production and production of sebasu cars , will also suspend its production of mini - cars from tomorrow , and will evaluate the situation on the 21st .
honda said that the operation of production lines relying on parts supply would be suspended next week .
the earthquake killed at least 10 people , injured more than 1,000 , collapsed hundreds of houses , and forced factories in the disaster area to stop operations .
indonesia bans sale of british brand name environmentally - friendly bags
indonesia has canceled the sale of british brand name environmentally - friendly bags following a rush to buy hong kong earlier this month , authorities said tuesday .
the person in charge of odyssey , located in indonesian plaza in the high consumption zone , said : " in view of the hong kong incident , we have canceled the listing of environmentally - friendly bags .
if the people hit hard for a bag of 140,000 rupees ( about 494 new taiwan dollars ) , it would have no value . "
thousands of hong kong people gathered outside the shop on the 6th , preparing to buy a limited environmental protection bag with " i am not plastic bags " designed by the british designer , named niyaz . however , the store refused to open the door , causing the scene to lose control .
the quality of the plastic bag , which was used for environmental protection purposes , unexpectedly became popular indicator in london and new york overnight , triggering an emergency purchase . the price on the auction site , the price has soared to several times the retail price .
odyssey , the only one to be sold in indonesia , said it was uncertain whether it would be sold in a few days ' time .
