insurance industry not to divert domestic stock capital in the short term : experts
chinanews , july 30 -
according to zhongguo zhengquan bao [ china securities news ] , the " provisional procedures on management of overseas investment of insurance funds " were promulgated a few days ago , and insurance funds have a broader space for use on the capital market .
liu lefei , chief investment officer of china life stock company , believes that the appreciation of the renminbi and the domestic capital market are good , and the insurance institutions will not invest in foreign currencies on a large scale in the short term . this also means that insurance will not flow into domestic stock markets in the short term .
the report says that many insurance institutions hold the same view .
experts say that since there is no market for the rmb derivatives , the insurance institutions have insufficient means to avoid risk , so the time is not yet ripe for a large - scale purchase of foreign exchange .
liu lefei said : from a long - term perspective , foreign investment should account for a certain proportion of the overall disposition of insurance companies .
however , due to the greater pressure of renminbi 's appreciation , china life insurance will mainly use its own foreign exchange funds to make overseas investment .
under the current circumstances , the purchase of foreign currencies for investment should be handled cautiously .
