do n't let traders trouble in public places
going out of the country for sightseeing is to relax , make clear , and enjoy to the greatest extent the fruits of natural scenery and social civilization .
however , many people have encountered such worries when traveling in china , and they are surrounded and intercepted by traders and intermediary businesses in public places .
whether it is cars or trains , and get out of the car , you always have to suffer from little traders and some dead - end fights without an intermediary .
it is not selling eggs , cooking cakes , selling newspapers and periodicals , and then introducing food and drink without an intermediary , or even selling fake certificates and invoices .
if you do not accept it , he can chase you for a few hundred meters , and if you are not successful , you will become a person of virtue .
in some scenic areas , many visitors also have the same feeling .
before entering the gate , people would sell such things as tourist souvenirs and handicrafts .
after entering the door , this kind of situation became even more serious , and no matter how good it was , it was thrown into confusion .
according to media reports , many foreign tourists visited xi'an , praising the scenic spots and sites there one after another , but they could not understand how many more small businessmen and hawkers were allowed to resell them everywhere .
public places such as stations and scenic areas , which are originally places for traveling and leisure , should stress civilization , orderly , quiet , and harmonious , and provide a comfortable and comfortable environment for tourists .
the free entry and exit of traders has disrupted the visitors ' feelings and , objectively , disrupted the public order of these public places and created visual pollution and environmental pollution . at the same time , it has also provided the conditions and opportunities for lawless elements to stir up trouble .
what is important is that these public places are windows of the building of the spiritual civilization in hong kong . peeping at the sight of the entire seal is not only an issue of image , but also an issue of impact on the development of the local economy .
just imagine , if you want to make a big and strong tourist industry , but use such a chaotic and chaotic tourist environment to welcome guests coming from the south and north , who will dare to come ?
how can your tourism economy obtain benefits ?
with the arrival of the peak tourist season , it should be said that it is an urgent task to create a civilized tourist environment for tourists from the north and south of the city .
public places are not markets , the business activities of small traders and hawkers should be regulated , those that operate without a license should be resolutely cancelled , and illegal activities should be resolutely cracked down on .
only a civilized and orderly environment can make tourists happy and return to the motherland with all kinds of youthful vigor .
in a word , do n't let traders trouble in public places .
" reward for voluntary retirement " could not stand consideration
the building of streets in dongcheng district in beijing is aimed at issuing refrigerators and other commodities as a reward for the 12 low - security families to take the initiative to retreat .
( " beijing news " 10 july )
this writer is happy about the improvement of the living conditions of these families . however , the formulation of " taking the initiative to withdraw from the insurance " and the practice of " giving rewards " are also complicated .
the deputy director of jianchuan neighborhood office said , " encouraging people to take the initiative to withdraw their insurance in view of such problems as fraud and minimal assurance is an example to other low - security households . "
if this model encourages other low - security personnel to extricate themselves from their predicament through their own efforts , it is indeed worth advocating , and if this is the case , those who want to " urge " those who have been cheating on low security over a long period of time will be a bit naive .
it is law that relies on more efforts to differentiate and clear away genuine and fake households .
departments concerned should strengthen the obligations to be carried out by low - protection households when enjoying low protection : for example , promptly informing family members and income changes , reporting on the employment situation , and receiving regular reexamination , the departments concerned should intensify supervision and inspection .
after all , it is a long - term plan to " withdraw from the insurance according to law . "
who will bury the material reward given to retired and protected families ?
as a first - level government organization , the streets are funded by financial resources .
should the taxpayers ' money not be spent ?
on the one hand , the withdrawal of low - security families proves that they already have a certain capacity to " be self - sufficient " ; on the other hand , is it not true that those applying for low - security assistance still exist ?
the government 's financial appropriations , which are called relief funds , should be delivered in snowy weather instead of adding fuel to the flowers .
