climate changes lead to rapid reduction in alps
xinhua news agency , geneva , july 29 th , by reporter jun liu
scientists of the swiss academy of sciences have conducted long - term tracking and research and found that more than 1,800 ice sheets in switzerland between 1850 and 2005 are decreasing at an average annual rate of 3 percent .
the heat wave in 2003 alone caused the glacier to melt 1.8% .
experts believe that by the 21 st century , if the global temperature rises by 3 degrees celsius , the glacier will decrease by 80 percent as compared with now , and the ice will melt further by 5 degrees celsius .
the glacier , the longest glacier in europe , has been listed in the unesco 's world natural heritage list , but it has been reduced by 100 meters in one year from 2005 to 2006 , and protecting the natural environment has become a matter of urgency .
the picture consists of 23 kilometers in length .
