( international ) study shows house shocks are related to two types of gene variations
xinhua news agency report of july 2nd from london - icelandic scientists have found through research that the risk of people suffering from housing fluctuations in two genes in their bodies is far higher than ordinary people .
according to a report in the latest issue of the nature magazine , researchers from iceland 's " fsla " have obtained the above discovery after screening several thousand genes from iceland , sweden , the united states , and hong kong , china .
these two genes found by scientists are similar to one that plays an important role in the early development of the heart .
shrapnel , one of the most common clinical allergies , can cause palpitations , rapid breathing , fatigue and pinch .
in addition , according to the report in the journal of natural clerosis published on the 1st , researchers from the company for diphtheria also found two genes on human chromosomes 17 , which played a certain role in more than one third of the front - profusion cancer cases .
the study also found that while raising the risk of people suffering from senile cancer , one of the genes also lowered the risk of diabetes ii .
