( international ) turkish ruling party wins parliamentary election
xinhua news agency report of july 30th from ankara ( by staff reporter wang jian ) - turkey 's supreme election commission released on july 30th the final results of the 23rd parliamentary election , which showed that the ruling justice and development party had won 341 seats out of 550 seats , once again winning the right to form a cabinet .
in the parliamentary election held on july 22 , the main opposition republican party won 112 seats .
the national action party won 71 seats in the election .
in addition to the three political parties mentioned above , 26 non - party members were elected .
the new turkish parliament will hold its first meeting on august 4 .
at that time , all members will be sworn in and will start to perform their duties .
after that , the parliament will elect a new speaker by secret ballot .
the turkish parliament election was scheduled to be held in november , but by the end of april , the parliamentary election had been moved forward because the opposition parties resisted the sole candidate , deputy prime minister and foreign minister of the justice and development party , resulting in the defeat of the presidential election .
